# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-SCRUB-03

Title
Modularize crushr-salvage and crushr-lab-salvage internals to reduce layered-patch breakage

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Reduce accidental breakage risk in the experimental salvage toolchain by splitting the two large salvage binaries into internal modules with preserved behavior.

This packet addresses a structural issue identified in hostile review:

- `crushr-salvage.rs` is too large and stateful
- `crushr-lab-salvage.rs` is too large and stateful
- new experiment formats are being added as narrow branches inside giant files
- builder touches one area and unrelated behavior breaks

This packet is a refactor/scrub packet.
It is not a semantics-change packet.

Primary goal:
- preserve current behavior
- shrink the abstraction surface
- make future experimental packets less fragile

